      "narrative": "Kappa of 0.180 falls in the 'Poor' band on the Landis/Koch scale. This reflects three structural factors: (1) the moderate class has only 8 samples (12.5% recall — v4.0 improved from 0% but remains limited by class rarity), (2) the model is intentionally conservative for regulatory screening (predicting high when uncertain), and (3) high-risk recall is 70.6% — the model correctly identifies most contaminated sites. For a protective screening tool, high recall matters more than balanced accuracy."
